post.description:
Sample request:

    POST api/v1/order
    {    
        "partnerOrderId": "Order-123",
        "subPartnerId": "SubPartner-123",
        "recipientBoxId": 123,
        "orderValue": 500,
        "recipient": {
            "fullName": "Jan Příjemce",
            "phoneNumberPrefix": "+420",
            "phoneNumber": "777888999",
            "email": "jan.prijemce@example.cz"
        },
        "sender": {
            "fullName": "Jan Odesílatel",
            "phoneNumberPrefix": "+420",
            "phoneNumber": "777999888",
            "email": "jan.odesilatel@example.cz"
        },
        "payment": {
            "price": 99,
            "variableSymbol": "123",
            "currency": "CZK",
            "refundBankNumber": "123456789/0100"
        },
        "currency": "CZK",
        "package": {
            "dimensions": {
                "depth": 15.6,
                "height": 12.3,
                "width": 7.8
            },
            "weight": 2.5
        }
    }

The top-level `currency` field is canonical. The nested `payment.currency`
field is kept only for backward compatibility and is deprecated. If top-level currency
is omitted, the request resolves to `CZK`.

get.description:
Sample requests:

    GET api/v1/order/Order-123/label
    GET api/v1/order/Order-123/label?subPartnerId=SubPartner-123
    
Base64 string label deserialization example:

    byte[] bytes = Convert.FromBase64String(base64String);
    string filePath = Path.Combine(Environment.CurrentDirectory, "label.pdf");
    File.WriteAllBytes(filePath, bytes);
